  "prompt": "Will it take 6 to 8 months to print all new notes and for normal economic condition?",
  "response": "The timeline for printing new currency notes and restoring normal economic conditions can vary widely depending on several factors, including the reason behind the issuance of new notes, the demand for currency, and the effectiveness of monetary policy during the transition.\n\nIf a country decides to change its currency or introduces new notes due to reasons like counterfeit prevention or economic reform, the actual printing process might take a few months to a year. However, achieving normal economic conditions can be a more complex issue influenced by factors such as inflation, public confidence in the currency, fiscal policies, and overall economic stability.\n\nIn summary, while printing new notes might take 6 to 8 months, achieving normal economic conditions could take longer and depend on numerous economic variables.",
